IN this country, towns and villages are normally named after the first inhabitants. They’re said to be drawn from the life experiences of those individuals. Many Ghanaians didn’t know of some weird village names until they were mentioned in Parliament. Everyone was left wondering about the origins of the names. People were surprised to hear the village name Etwe nim Nyansa means Vagina is Wise, Kote ye Aboa means Penis is a Fool, while Shua ye Morbor means Testicles are Miserable. According to graphic.com, these villages became known when the energy minister made a joke that providing them with electricity may interfere with night-time activities in the communities.   